rComments: great prof, and not that difficult of a course. Responds to emails like within the hour (if not instantly), and she's really helpful with homeworks. Just over all great lecturer too, great organization of the course. Take her
She's the best. So helpful. Probably best prof so far

Professor Martin-Perez, is one of the top teachers at the University of Ottawa for her pedagogy. She is very consistent in her approach, she does many examples in class, and she does not rush through the class material. She repeats things a few time and that's how you really grasp the subject. She explains step by step and everything is clear.
Clear lectures and notes. I like how she does a lot of examples in the lecture and also for tutorial to make sure we can understand the subject better.

Best engineering prof. Super clear, no surprises, what you see is what you'll get. If you get under an 8/10 in this class, that's your fault not hers. Fun truss project in this course as well. Would love to have her again!

I took a second-year course as a first-year student and I got so lucky to have her as my professor. The material is really challenging but she makes it so easy to understand. I've heard that she usually makes the midterm easy and then kills on the final but since I took it online it wasn't that bad. All in all, great prof :)
Prof. Beatriz is one of the best profs at the university, be sure to take her class if you have the chance! CVG 2140 has hard content, but Beatriz makes it so easy to understand

Prof. Beatriz knows the material like the back of her hand, and it shows. Her lectures are great and she explains things well. Be respectful in class, do the assigns yourself, go to office hours if you need to, and use her tutorial videos to study. She's also FTB even if you bomb the midterm, an excellent prof. Thank you Professor Beatriz!
Amazing prof. At first, I thought the course was just super easy, then I realized it was just because Beatriz was teaching it so well. A few assignments and a project, not too heavy.

So far the best professor Ive had at uottawa. If you can do and understand the online tutorials expect an A+. There is one team project that lasts the entire semester but its no sweat. Dont skip class unless you want to read the textbook which has a lot of unnecessary info. There arent any online notes.
Loved her!!! Everything is explained so clearly and it is easy to do well. She really cares for her students and she is hilarious. One of the best profs of the year

Great prof. She knows the content well and conveys what she knows just as well. The one bad thing about this course is that it's extremely heavy in content and there is a lot to learn and know. It's also worth noting that she has an awesome Spanish accent which makes the class that much more interesting.
Very professional. She is easily in the top 5 profs in CVG at UOttawa.

I've had the pleasure of having Dr. Martin-Perez for a bunch of undergrad classes and now a graduate one. Needless to say, she's one of the best prof of the Civil Engineering department. She's genuine, clear, and concise; 100% recommended.

SHE'S AMAZING!!! She made me love CVG 2140, she is a very nice lady and will take the entire class to make you understand something you didn't get if that's what it takes. She explains the material in a very clear and understandable way with a lovely accent. She's the best prof I ever had hands down!
BEST PROF IN CIVIL ENGINEERING! CLEAR LECTURES AND EASY MARKER! if you go to class and do all the assignments yourself... you are getting an A in the course .
Best prof in civil engineering hands down! her lectures get down to the point and are full of helpful examples!

the subjects she teaches have long exams, they are tough, but shes a very nice and very sweet person! very clear in teaching and shes usually not too bad in grading, makes midterm easy and kills everyone in the final but she bell curves.

The best professor in the whole faculty, clear , helpful, amazing in general. It is completely worth it to go to her classes and you will learn a lot. She is really helpful, will answer to your questions and is always there for you. Unlike other professors, she actually knows what is going on with assignments and labs.
Gives great lecture. Is clear with everything she presents and thorough with lab preparation.
The best Civil Engineering Professor at University of Ottawa.  Her written notes on the board are a work of art. Neatest I've ever seen.   Exceptionally nice too.

Excellent  prof. The course material itself was quite easy and very interesting. This prof was very nice and was always happy to help. Both the midterm and exam were straightforward but quite long. Some assignments were a bit tricky. Labs were easy and interesting, and very few people attended the DGD's although they were extremely useful,
Great prof! Very approachable and easy to talk to. Work hard in her class and you will be fine.
Great prof! Very approachable and easy to talk to. Work hard in her class and you will be fine.
Great prof! Very approachable and easy to talk to. Work hard in her class and you will be fine.
Great prof! Very approachable and easy to talk to. Work hard in her class and you will be fine.

professor is approachable and kind , however this class is pretty demanding. If  you don't have a good programming background the labs will take you a long time. The midterm was easy (high avg) since in the previous course(theory of structures 1 ) we learned about the stiffness method. However the final exam was not tough but very long, so beware.

She is a VERY good prof. Midterm was EASY like you wont imagine (the class average was in the '90s apparently), but come to the final, the material was easy but she made each question LONG, where you do not have time to finish. I believe this was made to bring down the class average to meet with regulations. But overall, a great class & prof!

Boring voice, great prof, easy going with marking, helpful and care for students!! but damn boring voice, her style of teaching its so hard to stay focused! but she tries very hard and its actually very clear if you can stay focused
Great prof. Wants you to actually understand the material, not just do the math. Explains concepts very well.
Great, sweet prof

Very professional Professor. Always very polite and helpful. Follow the methods and you will get an A. Very clear notes. Do the assignments, but don't talk in class, it gets her frustrated and things go downhill (mainly for you!)
Lovely lady. Does a solid job of being professional and friendly at the same time.
I love her... She's nice(maybe even too nice) and an easy marker. Perez will help you out if you go see her, super understanding.
She is great! Explains well and is willing to help you!!! She boosted everybody`s final mark by 5% before the final... That was nice.
Great prof and very helpful!

She is really nice and easy marker, but make sure to attend the lecs, because in the final there were 4 ques and one was from the lecs, which **** us up. any way make sure not to talk in the class. She doesnt like it
Excellent prof. knows what she is teaching and is very flexible and helpful especially in explaining and marking
